Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 3759/92 of 17 December 1992 on the common organization of the market in fishery and aquaculture products (1), as amended by Regulation (EEC) No 697/93 (2), and in particular Article 24 (2) thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1658/91 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3520/92 (4), introduced arrangements applicable until 30 April 1993 for retrospective Community surveillance of Atlantic salmon imports;
Whereas because of serious disturbance of the Community market for salmon the Commission has, by Regulation (EEC) No 3270/91 (5), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 992/92 (6), made Atlantic salmon imports subject to observance of a minimum price;
Whereas so that proper monitoring of the trend in Atlantic salmon imports can be continued and action taken to forestall any further deterioration in the market, the period of validity of the surveillance arrangements introduced by Regulation (EEC) No  1658/91 should be extended for eight months,
